Then like a moron, I decided to write in light with a firework inside a dark closed room - idiocy at its greatest. properties.title: Forgotten
properties.description: AJ Brustein posted a photo: This is Pullman Yard, an old freight train warehouse that is now locked down and inaccessible. That being said, it seems to be frequented by graffiti artists, druggies, the random photographer, movie crews, and odd couples on odd dates... Hit it up with a fellow Flickr buddy one Saturday afternoon. I left the entrance permit at home but I swear I had it... I'll do a short series of these shots, but could do a whole 365 here if I wanted to... This is cleanest, most friendly room in the whole place.

properties.title: 189/365 anticopizza
properties.description: ajbrusteinthreesixfive posted a photo: everyone loves pizza.But I especially love this one. I love American pizza - usually the thicker the better although a good slice from a local pizzeria or NY style is usually fantastic. But I also love real Italian pizza. And there are some decent choices in Atlanta to find them - but pretty sure Antico Pizza is the best. Best thing about it - chewy, not thin and flaky or dry like some others. And love that they have spicy olive oil (rare find in Atlanta) and even better, introduced me to putting salt on my pizza - fantastic. I always get the dried pepper too but never use it. The prices are high for Atlanta pizza, but totally worth it. ----- some books that have seen better days...

properties.title: Scratched
properties.description: andie1304 posted a photo: I have a bunch of DVDs that I have to destroy. My shredder doesn't shred DVDs. (Of course, I could buy a box of DVDs and scratch them to make a picture like this, but why would I do that?)
